dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: AP_ORDER
class.description: Representation of the non-linear geometric distortion -- inverse polynomial order of the first pixel axis.

class.title: A_ORDER
class.description: Representation of the non-linear geometric distortion -- polynomial order of the first world axis.

class.title: Airmass
class.description: This class describes parameters relevant to the airmass during observations.

class.title: BP_ORDER
class.description: Representation of the non-linear geometric distortion -- inverse polynomial order of the second pixel axis.

class.title: B_ORDER
class.description: Representation of the non-linear geometric distortion -- polynomial order of the second world axis.

class.title: Coordinate_Frame_Transformation_Matrix
class.description: Container class for the elements of a linear transformation matrix between the world coordinate frame and the pixel coordinate frame.

class.title: Distortion_Element
class.description: This class contains attributes for the axis, parameter, and value of an element in a PV distortion matrix.

class.title: Earth_Based_Telescope_Parameters
class.description: This class is intended to provide additional metadata for earth-based telescopic observations. Much of the information is geometry information, but in an earth-based context.

class.title: Instrument_Parameters
class.description: This class measures instrument temperatures, along with other potential instrument parameters that may affect the observation.

class.title: Observing_Conditions
class.description: This class details the quality of the product based on observational conditions.

class.title: PV_Distortion_Matrix
class.description: This class contains elements of a distortion matrix.

class.title: Pixel_Axes
class.description: Class containing attributes that link the value of ebt:pixel_axis_index with the horizontal and vertical axes of an image.

class.title: Reference_Frame_Identification
class.description: The Reference_Frame_Identification class is a base class for identifying reference frames. These are frames in the NAIF sense, i.e., three orthogonal axes with a specified orientation, but without a fixed origin.

class.title: Reference_Frame_Parameters
class.description: This class contains reference terms that define the WCS axes used in an image.

class.title: SIP_Distortion_Terms
class.description: This class contains subclasses representing the distortion terms used in the SIP standard.

class.title: SIP_Element
class.description: Class containing the value of an element of a SIP distortion polynomial, with element_value corresponding to the actual coefficient.

class.title: Seeing
class.description: This class describes parameters relevant to the seeing during observations.

class.title: Target_Geometry
class.description: This class contains attributes that describe angles and points in reference to the target.

class.title: Telescope_Geometry
class.description: The Geometry_Telescope class is a container for geometric information relevant to ground-based observations, as well as observations made from Earth-orbiting telescopes.

class.title: Transformation_Element
class.description: Class containing the value of an element of a linear transformational matrix between the world_axis_index and pixel_axis_index.

class.title: Weather
class.description: This class describes parameters relevant to the weather during observations.

class.title: World_Axis
class.description: This class contains attributes that describe an individual world axis as used in an image.

class.title: World_Coordinate_System
class.description: This class contains World Coordinate System (WCS) terms as specified by the FITS standard for the purpose of mapping the pixel coordinate frame of an image onto a celestial frame.

attribute.title: polynomial_order
attribute.description: Integer between 2 and 9 corresponding to the order of distortion polynomial in an image using the SIP standard.

attribute.title: polynomial_order
attribute.description: Integer between 2 and 9 corresponding to the order of distortion polynomial in an image using the SIP standard.

attribute.title: airmass
attribute.description: Amount of air along the line of sight when observing a celestial target. Equivalent to one divided by the cosine of the zenith angle (in degrees).

attribute.title: airmass_time
attribute.description: The airmass_time attribute specifies the time at which the airmass was measured.

attribute.title: polynomial_order
attribute.description: Integer between 2 and 9 corresponding to the order of distortion polynomial in an image using the SIP standard.

attribute.title: polynomial_order
attribute.description: Integer between 2 and 9 corresponding to the order of distortion polynomial in an image using the SIP standard.

attribute.title: element_value
attribute.description: The value of the matrix element corresponding to a given set of indices.

attribute.title: parameter_number
attribute.description: Integer between 0 and 99 corresponding to a particular non-linear algorithm used in a PV Distortion Matrix.

attribute.title: world_axis_index
attribute.description: An axis of the world coordinate system used for an image, corresponding to the 'i' in the CDi_j formalism.

attribute.title: apparent_visual_magnitude
attribute.description: The estimated magnitude at the time of observation as seen by the eye, or unfiltered observations.

attribute.title: instrument_temperature
attribute.description: The instrument_temperature attribute specifies the measured temperature of the instrument.

attribute.title: observing_notes
attribute.description: The observing_notes attribute is an optional field for describing the quality of the given observations.

attribute.title: photometric
attribute.description: The photometric attribute specifies whether observations at the time were considered photometric by the observer.

attribute.title: horizontal_axis
attribute.description: The ebt:pixel_axis_index corresponding to the horizontal axis of an image.

attribute.title: vertical_axis
attribute.description: The ebt:pixel_axis_index corresponding to the vertical axis of an image.

attribute.title: frame_spice_name
attribute.description: The frame_spice_name attribute is a NAIF-recognized string identifier for a reference frame associated with the data.

attribute.title: name
attribute.description: The name attribute provides a word or combination of words by which some feature is known.

attribute.title: comment
attribute.description: The comment attribute is a character string expressing one or more remarks or thoughts relevant to the object.

attribute.title: coordinate_system_celestial_pole_latitude
attribute.description: Latitude in the native coordinate system of the system's celestial pole.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: coordinate_system_celestial_pole_longitude
attribute.description: Longitude in the native coordinate system of the system's celestial pole.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: coordinate_system_equinox
attribute.description: Time origin of the coordinate system.

attribute.title: wcs_axes
attribute.description: A positive integer recording the number of WCS axes used in an image.

attribute.title: element_value
attribute.description: The value of the matrix element corresponding to a given set of indices.

attribute.title: p_polynomial_degree
attribute.description: Integer value representing the degree of the polynomial term in a SIP distortion polynomial, the p in, f.e. A_p_q.

attribute.title: q_polynomial_degree
attribute.description: Integer value representing the degree of the polynomial term in a SIP distortion polynomial, the q in, f.e. A_p_q.

attribute.title: seeing_full_width_half_maximum
attribute.description: This attribute specifies the FWHM of the seeing disk (e.g. a star).
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: solar_phase_angle
attribute.description: The solar_phase_angle attribute provides a measure of the relationship between the instrument viewing position and the sun. Solar phase angle is measured at the target; it is the angle between a vector to the sun and a vector to the instrument.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: subobserver_latitude
attribute.description: The subobserver_latitude attribute gives the value of the planetocentric latitude at the subobserver point on the target.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: subobserver_longitude
attribute.description: The subobserver_longitude attribute gives the value of the planetocentric longitude at the subobserver point on the target.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: subsolar_latitude
attribute.description: The subsolar_latitude attribute gives the value of the planetocentric latitude at the subsolar point on the target.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: subsolar_longitude
attribute.description: The subsolar_longitude attribute gives the value of the planetocentric longitude at the subsolar point on the target.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad

attribute.title: element_value
attribute.description: The value of the matrix element corresponding to a given set of indices.

attribute.title: pixel_axis_index
attribute.description: An axis of the pixel coordinate frame used for an image, corresponding to the 'j' in the CDi_j formalism.

attribute.title: world_axis_index
attribute.description: An axis of the world coordinate system used for an image, corresponding to the 'i' in the CDi_j formalism.

attribute.title: ambient_clouds
attribute.description: The clouds attribute specifies the measured percentage of clouds present during the observation.

attribute.title: ambient_humidity
attribute.description: The humidity attribute specifies the measured outside humidity during the observation, given as a percentage.

attribute.title: ambient_pressure
attribute.description: The ambient_pressure attribute specifies the measured outside pressure during the observation.

attribute.title: ambient_temperature
attribute.description: The ambient_temperature attribute specifies the measured outside temperature during the observation.

attribute.title: weather_notes
attribute.description: The weather_notes attribute is an optional field for describing the weather during the observation.

attribute.title: axis_index
attribute.description: Positive integer identifying which World_Axis is being described.

attribute.title: coordinate_name
attribute.description: Name of the celestial coordinate to which this axis corresponds.

attribute.title: coordinate_system_projection
attribute.description: Name of the coordinate system projection used for this axis.

PermissibleValue.value: Gnomonic with polynomial distortion plus SIP

attribute.title: horizontal_coordinate_pixel
attribute.description: horizontal_coordinate_pixel (sample) is the horizontal coordinate of a specific pixel.
attribute.unitId: DN, W/m**2/sr/nm/(DN/s), electron/DN, electrons, nm/mm, pixel

attribute.title: vertical_coordinate_pixel
attribute.description: vertical_coordinate_pixel (line) is the vertical coordinate of a specific pixel.
attribute.unitId: DN, W/m**2/sr/nm/(DN/s), electron/DN, electrons, nm/mm, pixel

attribute.title: world_coordinate_reference_point
attribute.description: World coordinate value at the reference point for this axis.
attribute.unitId: arcmin, arcsec, deg, hr, microrad, mrad, rad
